Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Place chicken breasts in a lightly greased 9x13 inch baking dish or roasting pan. Dot each breast with 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine, then season each breast with dried basil and garlic salt to taste. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for approximately 1 to 1 1/4 hours.